> Legend has it that before battle Hercules would stride into his kitchen and whip up a plate of this pasta to fuel his heroics. Since it was practically ready in the time it takes to cook the pasta, it meant he never missed the start of battle and firmly secured his place in the history books. Admittedly it's difficult to imagine the son of Zeus in a pinny, but you wouldn't catch us making fun of him.

Put a #large pot{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Once it comes to a rapid boil (i.e. lots of bubbles!) add the @wheat spaghetti{220%g} and cook for ~{10%minutes} or until 'al dente', remembering to save some pasta water for your sauce in step 5.

> It's 'al dente' once cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness in the middle.

Put a #pan on medium-high heat without any oil. Once hot add the @pine nuts{1%small pouch} and brown them off on all sides then remove.

> Watch your nuts like a hungry squirrel as the moment you turn your back they'll burn!

Peel and finely dice the @onion{1/4}(peeled and finely diced) and the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely diced). Chop the @red chilli{1/2}(chopped, seeds removed) in half lengthways and remove the seeds (if you don't like too much spice). Now finely dice the chilli and roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(roughly chopped).

> Don't stick your finger in your eye after chopping chilli. #Ouch!

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a pan on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook for ~{5%minutes} or until soft. Add the garlic and chilli and cook for a further ~{2%minutes}.

> Only use a small amount of the chilli if you prefer your dishes mild.

Add the @peas{1/3%pouch} and 3 tbsp of the pasta water. Allow to bubble away for ~{5%minutes} or until the peas are cooked.

Stir through half the tub of @creme fraiche{2.5%tub}, half the @hard Italian style cheese{2%tbsp}(grated) and the toasted pine nuts. Add @salt{to taste} and a few good grinds of @pepper{to taste}. Finally add a squeeze of @lemon{1/2}(juiced).

Drain the spaghetti and add to the sauce, mix well and serve with the chopped parsley and remaining Italian cheese over the top.